Standards… As content creators we create content based upon what attracts our viewers. And everyone’s concepts are different. Some people use shock or wow factors to build the momentum of the videos engagement. Some others choose to use a softer approach. We may not give it all to you in one video. Why? Because we are creating content. Keeping people interested or engaged. Did I refine this cut yes. Did I go in and clean up it up for the final result yes. Did I post it all here no. It’s broken into a series of 3 videos. Angry or understanding, Love it or hating the fact I cut her hair. It’s a thought provoking concept, that is content. Whether you understand that or not it is content made to create engagement. It’s a part of my career and I understand that.  Unfortunately other don’t because they don’t be knowing how to internet.

In my my years in this industry, I’ve found that we don’t take enough time to rest. 
I don’t mean completely unplugging, I'm talking about grabbing small moments within our day to simply let go. 
There are things we should definitely internalize and other things we most definitely should let go of in order to achieve the results we REALLY want. Here's what I mean. 
Internalize:
➡️ lessons that we learn and the steps we should take to grow from them
➡️ emotions that need to be processed and the why behind them
➡️ actions that lead to results 
Let go of:
❌ negative behaviors (especially of other people)
❌ situations out of our control 
❌ things that keep us stuck

Bonds That Matter
When we try to look into the lives of the Sahabah to find examples of brotherhood, it feels like a child in a chocolate shop being asked to choose their favourite chocolate. It becomes difficult to choose from.

But then you realise what a chocolate shop is about sweetness. It the same way with the Sahabah. It’s like their religion was tied around the brotherhood such that if you separated their religion from brotherhood, it becomes incomplete.

“Creeping upon you is the diseases of those people before you: envy and hatred. And hatred is the thing that shaves. I do not say it shaves the hair but it shaves the religion!

By the One in whose Hand is my soul, you will not enter paradise until you believe, and you will not believe until you love one another. Certainly, let me inform you of that which may establish such things: spread the greetings and peace among yourselves.” [Imam Ahmad and Al-Tirmidhi]

Brotherhood is a fundamental ingredient. It’s why the pillars of Islam are tied around the community.

“The believers are but brothers, so make settlement between your brothers. And fear Allah that you may receive mercy.” [49:10]

Lastly, the Prophet [Sallahu Alaiyhi Wasallam] said regarding companionship:

“A good friend and a bad friend are like a perfume-seller and a blacksmith: The perfume-seller might give you some perfume as a gift, or you might buy some from him, or at least you might smell its fragrance. As for the blacksmith, he might singe your clothes, and at the very least you will breathe in the fumes of the furnace.” [Bukhari, Muslim]

May Allah bless us with the best of companions Herenow and Hereafter.
